\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid13764832 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Could you tell me how many years you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Where I was born? I lived for seventeen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And then you went into the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Went into the Merchant Navy and came back after ten years and stayed in the same house again until 1935, that was - eight years. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The year of your birth was 1900?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And the year of your marriage 1930?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 1930, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 My birthplace was Greentown Walls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You had two half sisters did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Two half brothers and half sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Before you were born did your mother have any paid job or was she just on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Just on the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you have any idea how old she was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I would say about twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 After she married do you know if she had a paid job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How many rooms were there in the house you were living in at Walls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
There was - well really you could call - maybe call it for but - they - what we would now call garrets we actually used as rooms they were very low, just the - the room cei
ling of the - the - the slopping roof formed - formed off rooms, there was no side wall. And two - two rooms down below flat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the two rooms downstairs, could you tell me how they were used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. In our house the kitchen was fairly big, a lon
g shaped kitchen and on the end of the house - of the gable end of the house, of the kitchen I should say, there was double beds. What they called then in those days box beds. Which was beds with - wooden beds up against the wall and you could actually - 
t
hey had doors which you could close these doors, you could slide these doors, you could have closed it in completely like a box. And also there was one bed which was a single, not a - I mean a single storey bed, I should call it because it was a double be
d
 but as we know it today but there was also that single bed in the room as well, so that was three beds in the kitchen. Other - that still left quite convenient room in the kitchen. It was an open fire on the hearth, right on the hearth, built on the hear
t
h, and it was mainly peat of course was used, naturally in Shetland it was all peat. The - your cooking and your ate there and all. The other room was a much smaller room and I remember there was one bed in that room but it was more or less, it was much b
etter decorated, it was more or less used as a sitting room. Although it was only a case of strangers coming to the house - very special }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 strangers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  that you used it. But it was more or less done up in this day more in the state of a sitting room
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Like the parlour down South?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Something like that, yes. Now, again - oh that was in the lower flat. Then you went up a stair and these two rooms upstairs, I said they were very low, just forming V shaped roof so to speak and in one room was one bed and other
 room was more or less what you would call a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 lumber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did any lodgers live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was all relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you tell me what the household consisted of when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The household, when I was a child consisted of my grandfather and my grandmother. One, two, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  aunts, my mother and one uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they all sisters and a brother of your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's correct. That's correct.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No husbands of the aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the single bed in the sitting room, who slept in that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That was one of my aunts that slept in that bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Upstairs was my uncle as long as he could, in latter years I believe he slept down in the bed in the - what I - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  end, the sitting room, because he wasn't able to get up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Where did you and your mother sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Usually in one of the box beds, one of the double beds. Double - double height, not double width you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your grandparents have another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, they - they had another bed. There was another bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the other box bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the other box bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And the aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, there was two - very often two aunts sleeping together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your mother or grandmother pay anyone to help inside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. They did all their own work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, it was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your mother or grandmother or grandfather or anybody else, make clothes for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes, they all - all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 womenfolk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  made a certain amount of clothes. Everything - nearly everything in the knitted like was all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 made}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  by themselves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was made anything made by dressmakers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well there may have been - there would have been a very small amount of clothes bought from shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Readymade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Readymade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about tailors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh that - as far as I know - in my experience it was all bought readymade. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about mending clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh it was all mended at home, probably by - mostly the womenfolks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did the men do any mending or sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes, oh yes, they could - they could do and did do some - some of them and - I cannot just say specially if I remember any of them menfolks in the ho
use I lived, they didn't do very much of that you see there came to be two or three women in the house and the result was that it was nearly always passed on to the womenfolks. But - the men - the men were more or less engaged in the work around the croft
 
during - say for instance, during an evening. Well - there was very little social life around unless a few gathered together and the result was that these men - well grandfather he was probably repairing herring nets. Or he may have been making rope or si
mmonts as we called it, it was like ropes for tying down the corn and everything you see, these kind of things, that was their evening work and that was more or less the menfolks took part in that whereas the women either did knitting or mending clothes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they make the baskets for fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, oh yes. Oh yes, they made - they did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's wasn't the women's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, that wasn't the women's job, that was always done by the men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember if the shoes were mended in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Shoes were always mended in the home yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Who did that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well as far as I remember my grandfather generally did that. I couldn't just say offhand who did it after that. There was - boot repairers not - shops, not boot repair sho
ps, but - odd people who did a little bit of shopping - shoe repairing. In the village. So I wouldn't just like to say if - I would visualize that any kind of rough shoe would have - was repaired at home and anything in the more sophisticated line was sen
t out to the repairers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were any secondhand clothes bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Not much. Oh no. That was - that was something I - that's very good question because - there was - very very - reluctant to buy secondhand clothes. They never - they never - didn't like 
that the others were frightened that there was some disease in them or something of that kind you know. I don't - well partly that and partly I might say a sort of pride that they wouldn't humble themselves to buy secondhand clothes. So I couldn't - I cou
ldn't say that in the - in the district at all that you ever heard hardly of anybody buying secondhand clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 Jumble sales}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  weren't so popular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, such a thing never was known about then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So shoes were bought were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Mostly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 nearly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 all shoes were bought yes. In fact I'm afraid in our hose it would all have been bought because although shoe repairing was done in our house I know but I cannot say that ever anyone made shoes, except, mind you, rivalins. The more or less the moccasin. 
That was I suppose made in the home - in our house, maybe menfolks always made that themselves. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Out of sheepskin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, cowshide. Aye, cowshide.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you wear clogs in your family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much. Never except occasional
ly maybe just around the - going in the byre or something of that kind, you never - you never took the - you never wore them any further away from the house such as round the croft you never wore them. You just - maybe going to meet - feed the cattle or s
omething of that kind you'd maybe wear them but never - never any further.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And not in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, not in the house, oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there any particular season of the year or time when you had new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I wouldn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the south they have this custom of getting new clothes for Whitsun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes, I know, yes. No I'm afraid that there was nothing of that kind. No, I think it was just - new clothes were bought when they were - actually required.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did the menfolk help the women with any jobs indoors, for example leaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Not very much. Not that I ever saw in our house, no, that was - I don't think the menfolks ever had it to - oh they might occasionally have done little bit of washing up or that, but
 generally speaking cooking, no. No, cooking, they was never - they might have prepared such as - fish or that, they might prepared it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You mean taking the bones out and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well gutting - guts out and such like they might have done that, but as far as cooking, no, it was always left to the women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Is the same true of cleaning, the women did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, nearly always. Except when it came to - anything such as papering or - that kind of thing, but - the general clean - sa
y sweeping or dusting or something like that, no, always the women. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did the women do the decorating too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, very - oh well that was I would say a mixed occupation because - generally you saw women having a go at it but men I think more or 
less did it but - the women often had a go at that too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And repairs, suppose something broke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That was always the menfolks job. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about keeping the fire going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well anyone did that, that was just - anyone that was handy did that, didn't matter about whether it is was women or men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you were a child did your grandfather or your uncle, the one you thought of as a father, dress you or undress you or do any }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  those sort of things for you, bath you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, but 
of course in my - really as - as a child before schooldays and like of that my mother was still with me you see. And she looked after all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you ever remember any of the menfolk telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What kind of stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
More or less seamanship stories. Stories from the sea was nearly - well him being a - former Merchant Navy man I mean it was - that was - main stories was about the sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about ghost stories, did you ever have any ghost stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes. Oh I had quite a few of them too. They - they - they were very very rampant all around everywhere - wherever - mostly these were told when you got - some people coming into your house at night which - of course then a days you didn't have - mea
n you were lucky if you had - maybe one or two dances through a whole winter and you - the - occasionally a wedding or something like that. Otherwise it - you had all to make your own sport and your own house with few neighbours. And these were the times 
when the womenfolks gathered in and took their knitting and suchlike. Then of course all these ghost stories of things of that kind went very high then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about reading aloud, were any books read to you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Yes. I remember my uncl
e very often reading to me. And I do think that I I've often - often felt that I got - in my very early days I got as much book training and - three R's as you might say - I got as much training from my uncle as ever I got from the teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did he teach you to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
He did, he'd teach me to read and - I remember very very often having all my - lessons at - my exercises that were given me from school, he saw that all that exercises was carried through and helped me with them where I needed help bu
t - not unnecessarily, I mean to say - always saw that I did my part. I mean he didn't just take my place, he didn't take my place in it, he did - he saw that I did the thing but he did - he saw that I - really understood what I was doing. I think I learn
ed as much from him as ever I did from the teacher for the first few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were lucky to have someone like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was I admit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your grandfather also tell stories and read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, he did but I don't remember so much of t
hat. I remember one or two maybe that he told but - I think he was more - even more of a storyteller than ever my uncle was but I was too young to remember them again. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How old were you when he passed away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I think that I would have been roughly about ten years old maybe or thereabout, ten to eleven year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well my grandmother had died before that, she would - I don't - I don't know if I'd been going to school when she died. I was quite - very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your uncle ever take you out on your own anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, well he couldn't - he couldn't very well you see because he had just one leg and the other one was what we called them days a pin leg, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But you used to spend time with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, very much so. Spent a tremendous amount of time in his workshop, joiner shop, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Making the little cups and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh all little things like that, oh yes, yes, spend an awful lot of time around there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you were a child did you have any tasks you had to regularly to help the adults in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I shouldn't say that I did, no. No, I couldn't say that I'd any actual tasks set me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But you did help did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I did - yes, I helped, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What sort of things did you help with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well - I was always interested among the animals you know, such as - sheep and cattle and these kind of things and would have always helped the - there was - it was always a - see there was practically everything they
 could cultivate was cultivated but round the borders of these small plots that we called the rigs, around these borders was - grew up beautiful grass. And very often you had to take the cow on the tether and see that she kept on this grass you see, kept 
her off of going in among the corn and the turnips or the potatoes. That was a job that I remember me being quite interested in, I would sit with that cow for maybe hours. And - see that she didn't trespass onto the - potatoes or corn or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were telling me about the sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes. Aye, well the sheep - I was quite interested in sheep but - when I came back from the Merchant Navy, back to the croft again I found that sheep was - well, they seemed to interest me somehow or other. The resul
t was I took quite an interest in sheep and had quite a number of sheep and - in my own name although I just left them behind like to my uncle when he took - took over the croft and I went out from it because I couldn't take them with me. But - quite a nu
mber of sheep just that I had reared from buying at sales and - then prospering and having plenty of offspring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 As a child did you also work with sheep at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, to a certain extent. Of course you always took - you took the lambs in you see
 at a certain period in the harvest then you - you took this lambs and you kept them in the house, you put them out on a fine day, then you had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 lots}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  of days with snow and suchlike and you just kept them in and fed them, hand fed them. And with - with these lambs around the croft I was always interested in that of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You used to feed them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Anything indoors, or did the womenfolk do all the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, practically everything - all the cleaning and everything was done by the women - foil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any hens on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Ducks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Ducks, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you look after those at all or collect eggs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But it was mostly with the cow was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Cows and sheep and such like that - I never remember another thing that we used to have these days was geese. Ah yes. We had geese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What were they kept for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well, you keep - kept them and reared them up you know and then sold them at Christmastime. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you eat them yourselves too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were the eggs eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Eggs - no eggs was - well a certain amount was - you mean - oh the eggs of the geese. No, no, the eggs of the geese was generally reared, you generally had your two or three parents and - and the - they reared up the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 youngsters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  and you - then you fattened them up and sold them at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The eggs aren't used for the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were the only small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was, yes, I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you expected to go to bed at a particular time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there any rule about bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. There wasn't. No, not like we know it today, there was - there were none of this - go to bed at eight
 o'clock or something like that. No, no, no, there was nothing that you could - if there was something going on in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 house, at lot of people in and the like that that was nothing unusual you might have been up to midnight. Ah yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you did go to
 bed, when you were quite a small child, did your mother or anyone else put you to bed or did you just go off on your own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But it was mostly with the cow was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Cows and sheep and such like that - I never remember another thing that we used to have these days was geese. Ah yes. We had geese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What were they kept for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well, you keep - kept them and reared them up you know and then sold them at Christmastime. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you eat them yourselves too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were the eggs eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Eggs - no eggs was - well a certain amount was - you mean - oh the eggs of the geese. No, no, the eggs of the geese was generally reared, you generally had your two or three parents and - and the - t
hey reared up the younger and you - then you fattened them up and sold them at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The eggs aren't used for the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were the only small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was, yes, I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you expected to go to bed at a particular time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there any rule about bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No. There wasn't. No, not like we know it today, there was - there were none of this - go to bed at eight o'clock or something like that. No, no, no, there was nothing that you could - if there was something going on in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  house, at lot of people in and the like that that was nothing unusual you might have been up to midnight. Ah yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you did go to bed, when you were quite a small child, did your mother 
or anyone else put you to bed or did you just go off on your own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well - it depended a lot of course if there was people in and you maybe began to get sleepy and - you maybe tuned away on your own or - if there was nobody in - your mother or aunt or
 someone probably put you to bed. Just depended a lot on what was going on in the house at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you tell me about what the system was in those days for bathing, was there a weekly bath or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No, no, no. You would j
ust - you had a wash and - occasionally of course when you - especially when you were really young you - always had a bath of course, you - daily bath when you were really young. But later on it just become a case that you - well - you bathed when you sor
t of felt like it or when the people thought you needed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The family ate in the kitchen and you said very occasionally the sitting room was used, did people ever have meal in it in your family?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I shouldn't - they never had meals in it. They may have just - a sort of cup tea or something like that and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When was breakfast eaten, was there a particular time of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, I would say in - in our house - about - between nine and ten was fairly regular. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Who was present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well, all - everybody, it was - unless they was away from home, everyone that was - at home would be there at table, breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What was usually eaten at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well you may have - there never was anything very spec
ial. It depended of course a lot you see you - something - you nearly always had your own pig. Yes, you nearly always had your own pig. Well you see, that meant to say that you had pork. And ham nearly any - times so very occasionally - occasionally, mayb
e
 - I wouldn't say too - often, but occasionally you might have a - a slice of pork or bacon. At breakfast, or you might just have had a boiled egg or something like that. There were just - there was always plenty of homemade bread. Home baked bread and pl
enty of homemade butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It must have been delicious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, it was quite good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have porridge at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Some did but I can't remember an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 awful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  lot of that in our house. No, but I know that there were some houses where it was very much used, it was a sort of a regular thing for breakfast. But I - never remember much of it in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about on Sundays for breakfast, was there anything different as a rule on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I wouldn't say that there was very much different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you drink tea at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What was the next meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh the next was dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There wasn't anything in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. Nothing in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And dinner was eaten at what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I would say about two o'clock. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was it the same that anyone around would be there at the dinner table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Every body - everyone would be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What sort of food did you eat at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well very often it was either - e
ither fish or mutton. You always had mutton in some shape or form handy anyway, you either had it in the fresh state or else - in the dried and salted state. Or you had fish of course, you were always - you can catch your own fish them days too, it was - 
either you or some neighbour or something. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 It was - there was generally always fish handy so it would - it would generally be fish or - or mutton and always plenty of taties.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was the fish ever salted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh the fish was salted, dried and salted very very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Hung up on lines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, that's correct, oh yes, very - nearly every house had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about other vegetables besides potatoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, you - you very often had cabbages. You had cabbage always hunted out and go
t the ones with the good firm hearts, centre bulb in them and - turnips and - maybe occasionally carrots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Any salad food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No, not very much, no, I wouldn't say there was every anything - I don't think I ever saw anything of that kind until I
 came away from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there a pudding or dessert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No. No, very seldom. Very very seldom. It was nearly always just a - a cup of tea and a - maybe - might - might have been jam, maybe your homemade jam or something just on bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was cheese ever eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. I never - I - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 scarcely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  ever tasted cheese 'til I come away from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It wasn't made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, it wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was that general in Shetland do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I don't think there was an awful lot of cheese ever made in Shetland. Orkney yes but not Shetland, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 After that meal what was the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Next one was tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And that was about when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well anytime from - anytime -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What was usually eaten at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There never was very much excepting
 we had boiled eggs or something of that kind, you never had anything big, just plenty of bread and butter and - yes, you occasionally had jam. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, but - you see very often you'd jam, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Any kind of oatcakes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh oatcakes was always in plentiful supply.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Tea again to drink with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Always tea, always tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did anybody drink a glass of milk or cup of milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Occasionally. I never remember it very much done in our house but I know that there was plenty of people who drunk a lot of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you given milk as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there anything different on Sundays for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well Sunday very very often it was - what - sound peculiar to you but what we called tatie soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Is that potato soup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes. Now that was - different from what you would maybe understand as potato soup. It was - the potatoes was just cut in two or three and they're boiled with a big jug of mutton and of course i
f they boiled it long enough they began to split up more or less and it did - did come to be soup eventually. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 
And that was very, very often the - either you would have that, big plate of that, or else - you might have had mutton and taties. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And usually whe
n you did have taties it was always with their jackets on. You - I mean you - you - skinned them, you - but they were boiled with their jackets on. Fact of the matter I still told this day I like a tatie with their jackets on and take it - skin them for o
urself in a bowl, I always think they're better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It keeps the flavour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It does, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there anything different at teatime on Sunday or was that just the usual?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I wouldn't say there was anything different no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were any sort of sweet cakes ever baked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Not very much. They might - you might have got anything just with a few currants in it or - maybe sweetened with a little bit of plain sugar. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not icing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, there was nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was that the last meal of the day or was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982  there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  supper as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh no, we had supper. The fact of the matter - although I didn't - it wasn't done in our house but I know a supper was sometimes a very very heavy meal, it was maybe a whole plate of soup of something
 of that kind, tatie soup, yes, yes, it was a very heavy meal sometimes. I don't know how they got on with it but - I - I never remember that being in our house. It was just - just maybe a cup of milk or a cup of tea or something of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not even anything to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well, yes, we just had a bit of plain home baked bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But not cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not cooked, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your mother or father bake their own bread, bread was baked in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh well they would be - they done baking every day. Oh every day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was jam made by the womenfolk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes. Usually it was and most crofts always had a certain amount of rhubarb. That - that was about the only jam that I ever remembered - made was rhubarb jam. And that any other jam that was in the house would have been bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Jam was bought sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, occasionally, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any things like blackberries or berry fruits, bramble and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was - there - you could have got blackberries and suchlike but I - I never remember much of it made into jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they eaten fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They were eaten fresh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 An I right in saying a lot of the time you had no fresh fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not a - not very much. Not very much at 
all. That - in fact of the matter I never knew much about that until I came away from home out and landing out amongst strangers. And long time and such like before I knew much about the fresh fruit and suchlike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Could it be bought in Walls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You
 could, oh yes, you could have bought apples and suchlike. And occasionally you did buy maybe an apple just to - that was - sort of a rarity to have an apple at all. But, oh yes, they generally could buy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But it wasn't part of the day to day diet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. Oh definitely not, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were any vegetables preserved, bottled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. Never in - never in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were pickles made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was anything brewed, beer or any sine made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not - not in our house. No, never - in fact of the matter I don't think there was anything of that in Walls at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about medicines or remedies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well there was, yes, there was a lot of the old fashioned remedies you know and - there were a certain amount of them that I couldn't expl
ain that, I - I wouldn't go deeply into that but there was a certain amount taken from roots of herb roots and - but it was - a subject that I couldn't discuss because I know it was done but I - couldn't - couldn't go deeply into it. It was done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about gruel, I don't know what they call it on Shetland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, well gruel, it was gruel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you given that for colds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, occasionally. I don't think I liked it very well but I didn't very often get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember any vegetables }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  being bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I wouldn't say that I can, no, I doubt - we always - always grew our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Anything out of tins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No, I - I hardly ever saw anything out of tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I - certainly there was core
d beef to be had - I remember on one occasion having corned beef and - was sorry for it anyway. Traveling from Lerwick to Walls and - we took as our lunch break we took a tin of corned beef and a bottle or two of lemonade or something. By }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 Jove}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 , I - I wasn'
t well after that I can assure you. But I - I remember that corned beef was bought in Lerwick, it wasn't - it wasn't bought in Walls, it was bought in Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Pulses and dried peas and lentils, did you have that in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I can say I've seen
 lentils but I couldn't say that ever I saw much about much of peas or beans and nothing of that kind and things. But, lentils, yes, I did see lentils occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was it made into soup in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you ever get rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. We detested rabbits, we didn't like rabbits at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did some people eat them round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I think - well I couldn't say, I don't know but I don't think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They weren't popular?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They weren't - no, they were not popular. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you took a rabbit was it considered poaching or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, I don't think anybody bothered if you did take a rabbit, you just took it and that was that, I - I don't think there was anything, no, I never heard anything about that in them days at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about eating wild birds, shooting birds and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh well, I didn't - never heard much about that either, I mean to say you could shoot them - shoot wild birds and - just as you liked.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you say that in your family that there was plenty of food or was there sometimes not enough for everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, I think there was always plenty. I couldn't say that our house was a house where there was very much money coming into. But - there was always a very good supply of ou
r own home grown stuff. And we always had our pig and sheep and something of that - and fish and suchlike which was - saved you from spending a lot of money, but I - I wouldn't say our house was ever - had a plentiful supply of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember there being a real lack of money so there was sometimes a lot of anxiety about rent or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 No, I don't think so, you see, rents was very, very moderate. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
A croft rent was extremely moderate. It's only a matter of two or three pound a year you see. Yes. And then I - I never - well there may have been - unbeknown to mean a child but - there may have been anxieties at times but I never heard it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was no need them for your grandmother or aunts or mother to stint themselves 
of food so that you could have more or the menfolk could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I don't think there was ever anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you allowed to talk at the meal table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Could you choose what you wanted to eat, if there was something you didn't like could you refuse it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well, yes, you could refuse it. I don't - you wouldn't have - refused it too often, I mean, they - they would certainly have clamped down on you if you made a practice of it but - still they - it wasn't - I couldn't
 say that ours was a very strict home. Oh no, by no means.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you left your food on the plate, they didn't punish you for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, oh no. No. They wouldn't punish you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they particular about the way you held your knife and fork or didn't they mind about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They weren't fussy about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, they're not fussy at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well you could leave table any time you liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You didn't all have to wait until you'd all finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have to ask or did you just get down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, you would - I never remember any time when you had to ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did everyone keep to the same place always at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Very much so. Seemed to be that - 
that seemed to be - well I don't think anybody would ever have said, you're in my place, or something of that kind, but - you just more or less went to your place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was the meal served by several of the womenfolk or was there one particular woman who always served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Very often it was one particular because - you generally had one which took the household chores. For instance, in our house I remember very well - that - there was the three - my three aunts there for instance. Well one of them was nea
rly always inside woman, the other two was always working outside, and that was the one that would have prepared the meals and - well, generally speaking served them as well. That one, the other two, well they'd be working outside all day and they come in
 the same as the menfolk would have done and - and sit down and had their meal in peace and quiet and the other would have - the household woman would have done the serving.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well as far as I remember of her, I dinna 
remember an awful lot about her, she died pretty - when I was pretty young but - I - I've a feeling that she was come to state that she wouldn't have been asked to do very much as ever I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 She'd have mostly been sitting indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I think more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your mother work outdoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes, yes, oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Could you bring toys or a book to the table if you'd wanted to at a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I suppose you could but I don't think it would have been really acceptable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I couldn't remember me ever doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If there was salt on the table, if you wanted it, could you ask for it to be passed or did you just take it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well if you - you could reach it you just took it, you didn't ask anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If it was out of reach you asked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Your ideas of right and wrong and how to behave, who would you say you got them from the most in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I - I couldn't remember - anything about 
that up to school days. Couldn't say if I remember much but during schooldays I think that there was no one that kept me more - in the right path than what my - uncle did. And there was one of my aunts which - I generally leaned towards and - I believe th
at she did take more interest in me than the other two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was she an indoor one or outdoor one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
She was the indoor one. Until later years and then she had to go to as well and work outside too and when there was plenty of them like then she was inside one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Can you remember the kind of things which they did, by example or by what they said, convey to you as important, the sort of things in life which were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - they definitely - there was - I mean, you'd - although there wasn'
t maybe the - the stress put on the Christian life as what was put in some homes but that was very much stressed on you. Christian principles. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 
Likewise - right and wrong as you would say in telling the truth and - and being kind to people who wasn't - who was worse than yourself or - any deviltry or - these things was very much stressed to you.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was tolerance of other people a thing which you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Well there was of course - you wouldn't - that wouldn't have applied very much except where
 a person was - say a lady was disabled or had any - otherwise you didn't need to be tolerant as you would say because there wasn't like a class distinction among or anything of that kind like the colour bar or anything of that kind which would maybe lead
 to that question but that wasn't the case you see. Not with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there no class distinctions in Walls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well there was a lot of class distinctions, oh definitely. But - very much so and an awful lot more than what there is these days. Th
ere was these certain people which of course was just considered - well, you would never have dreamed of - taking them as equals. No, they was a step above you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh the shopkeeper, the minister, the schoolteacher - the likes of these people were definitely in the better class. Oh yes, very much so.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did their children go to school with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How did the children react?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Children didn't seem to make much difference. In their schooldays but -
 immediately they came out of school if they came in their teenage days then you began to see the difference right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about when they visited in the evenings, would those people you've just mentioned not visit the crofters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. Oh no, no. Definitely not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And the same would apply, you wouldn't go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  their homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You wouldn't be going to their houses. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you tell me a little bit more about that, were you made to feel you were their social inferiors in their eyes in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh very much so. Oh you - you very - you very much - you were very much so. Well it was just sort of taken for granted. You - you were - made to feel that you were very nearly - taken for granted you knew it right from the beginning.
 That you - they were your superiors so to speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you tell me about how people addressed each other in Walls in the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I'm afraid that that - the same as your talking about now would have applied, I mean so and so would have 
been Mr, you would never have dreamed of saying that here's Manny or Geordie or something of that kind, you would never have thought about calling them by that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 
But - when you came - of course all - that was one thing that was very, very much adhered to, I don't - I don't ever remember being instructed in that line but you just naturally fell to anyone getting a wee bit up in years was always respected.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Whatever their social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Whatever their social class but - I think they way that I would f
eel about it was that - the so called better class or would have liked to have themselves that, that you felt more like ignoring them than you - than - than - specially picking them out with Mr and Mrs something of that kind. You - you felt more like just
 trying to pass them by, you know, you're different class, you don't want to bother me and I don't bother with you so to speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you went to church did you meet that type of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, you met them but - I'm afraid that the same status symbol still remained - even in the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was the seating according to social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes. They would - for the general rank and file it would be a case of - you'd have gone into any seat that was vacant but the - these better class, so - so called b
etter class would have definitely had their seat and they would see that they got that seat and - they would - wouldn't have looked very nicely at you if you were in their seat, they maybe just wouldn't have told you to get out of it but still the - they 
- they would have made you feel it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they pews that they paid for was it liked that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I don't think so in our church. I don't - I don't think that. Actually - I was - my - I - I went to Methodist Sunday school and - I still - in fact if I did
 go - well I'm nothing now, I never - I'd refuse to attend a church of any kind. But - I think it - I still have a leaning to - to Methodist even yet although I've been associated with the Church of Scotland for many years now, but - I've still got a lean
i
ng. And my - my - I went to Methodist Sunday school. But - the same thing applied, I don't think I can ever remember seats being paid, I know in the church that I've - I'm associated with now at one time the seats was marked and - and paid for and all. Bu
t they're - they're not now of course, not been for many years. But I know that was the case in the church where I'm associated with now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there anybody you had to call sir, or it was expected of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I don't think so, not in - not in our little village. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not the minister even?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. I don't think so. Well you would have done it to your own teacher of course, in school. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there a big landowner around - a Laird.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well not except the landowner - there wasn't ma
ny landlowners, generally their factors was there. He was always one of the sort of better class. He was acting factor for the landlord. In Walls of course one of the landlords that owned a good part of Walls had his own island. And a villa. The Island of
 Vaila.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Which Island is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
That's the Island that lies off the - entrance of - close in the harbour of Walls. There's two islands there, the bigger - the bigger one out - outside one is Vaila and the inside one is Linga. And that island belong
ed to the chief Anderton. And the fact of the matter his, I think it was his sister, I'm not sure about this but I think it were his sister just died just a matter of a few month ago was the last inhabitant of - was the last one of that race I think to be
 inherent. But I don't know, I mean, it's something I couldn't go into but that is - it was Anderton that he owned the - quite a considerable amount of Walls anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you ever meet him, did he ever come and sort of mingle with the people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, oh no, no, no, no. No, they more or less -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 He kept quite a part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did he go to church in Walls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, well you see the island hadn't been the island he wouldn't have been much at church anyhow. But - he come - came out occasi
onally but - out from the island and they had their own launch and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 such like}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 but - I couldn't say if ever I had any - much knowledge of them at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did he play an important part in the so called better class people, was he one of the social leaders or was he rather apart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I think he would have been more or less apart. Apart from all that - any of these so called crowd - whether - whether they're the poorer class or the richer class, there were - maybe not richer or poorer but better class and th
e - I don't - think he would have mixed much with any of them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would he have considered himself above them do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I rather think so but I - I know there was a - a lot of his life I think it was spent in Bradford. He had a lot to do wi
th wool mills in Bradford, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 As a young lad, was the term working class a term that people used in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, not exactly. Not in - not in the form what they use it now. You were - well of course there's an awful lot of the things as you
 fully appreciate, a lot of the things that we know about, we read about and we hear about today that - just - never was thought about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You and your family and people didn't think of themselves with a label in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh - no, I don't think th
ey did. I - well of course I - our family was a - a peculiar family in a way because - I don't know if they would really have been called the lower class, if you want to put it that way, because my uncle being a joiner and he was doing a - they had to be 
obliged to have occasionally for work you see. And my grandfather, again he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 boat builder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 and suchlike and went to fishing and - even built houses and things of that kind, well again he - here was something they had to be obliged to look for. So in a way we had a certain amount of contact with this better class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there other families too who were on hour sort of level of contact?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 There}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  would have been, there would have been an occasional one or two, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  See we had a - our house - was I 
believe one of the earliest houses that had the wooden - wooden roof. But for the simple reason why that my grandfather was a builder in their own rights and the result was he could do it himself. Felt covered of course. But wooden roof and it was - it wa
s
 one of the earlier wooden roofs there was in Walls. So I suppose that in that light too that even our house would have been a wee bit - maybe thought by some people, I've never heard them say it, they wouldn't think it today of course but - at that time 
p
robably it could have been more or less maybe looked at as one of the better class houses. Just for the simple reason that they had got that title - that one little step ahead you see, that they had got a wooden roof on their house, wood covered with felt
, rather than the thatched roof.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. Not as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember on any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 occasions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  anything that marked it as different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well you may - very occasionally have a few of your chums in just for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 
wee bit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  party. When you - in your early school days. Later on you didn't matter much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you had a bit of a party what sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh well, just maybe - have a wee bit better grub and - a few sweet things and - ah well, the usual kiddies games you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You'd have games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would any of grown ups organise you or would you just play on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, more or less just play on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not these organised affairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No, no, no. You never had much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember anything that happened on Christmas Day that's different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That definitely was something different but I just can't recall very much outs
tanding. I never in my early days I didn't know very much of the visiting, or anything of that, I didn't - never noticed much of it in our house, I think it did go on but - I cannot recall much visiting or - or maybe going round with a bottle or something
 of that kind. I couldn't say that I ever I recall much of it in our house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Visiting on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
On Christmas Day. Of course - well, yes, in the early days Christmas was I think more respected and thought of in the country district than it is now, now it is more or less the New Year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was it less so when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
It was less so, it was the - the Christmas was the - the Christmas was more thought of than what the New Year was. Now it's come to round the other way. Christmas doesn't count so much}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 
 except}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  maybe for anyone - going to a friends for dinner or something of that kind, otherwise it's all New Year, especially taking in the New Year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember any New Year celebrations when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I could
n't say that I do, somehow or other it seems if there was any celebration of any kind it was Christmas. Yes. It was Christmas, in the early part of - as different from now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the home were there any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well there was no musici
ans exactly in our house at all you see. I think the first thing that I - this is first one that had any inclination to a little musical or any contact with any musical instruments was myself. I did - in a very very small way I began to get interested a l
ittle bit in music. I can't remember - there was one or two of us with reasonably good voice, good singers but I never remember any music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No fiddle or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, there was no fiddle until - until I came along with one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And that was when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I should say - I got a fiddle - in - sometime in my early teenage, I just forget when, but previous to that I had had an accordion.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were saying about the fiddle?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, I - I used to do a little on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 melodeon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 . And - my -
 I had an aunt, well, it was uncle's wife like, in the island of Vaila and there was a unfortunate incident in Vaila where - the boatmen there committed suicide. And when he - when this happened then the folks of the house they didn't feel like keeping an
y of his musical instruments, he was very musical. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 And all his instruments was of a very, very hight standard. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
And they gave most of it to my aunt. Especially the fiddle. Now she could do a little on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 melodeon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 and she said if I would give her the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 melodeon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  she would give me a fiddle. And I have that fiddle to this day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You learnt to play it then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well, yes, to a certain extent, I - the - I've often been insisted on to coming with the fiddlers group but - I had one defect which I've never
 got over. If a fiddle was properly tuned to me I could play a - reasonably well once upon a time, but I was no used tuning it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Who was it taught you how to play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh nobody at all, I just - picked it up. Yes, yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 
No, I think there were very few - in that - - them days that had much teaching, it was just a case of picking it up when - when - from someone - someone older and - and hearing the tunes played here and there you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you ever make music together in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I couldn't say they ever - not to do that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not even singing hymns or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. I never noticed that maybe they prayed more or less individually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did anyone in the family play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I never remember very much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have snakes and ladders, ludo or cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No. No, very little of that either, it was just - more or less physical games. Especially outside games and - there may have been a very little of the cards or - card or board games on winter nights but I - I never remember very much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about ball games outdoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not - not very much, no, the - football wasn't taught very much, there wasn't any interests in football or anything of that kind of course
 the likes of things which you see nowadays, I mean to say, such as basketball or - or - even - tennis or anything of that kind that was - oh of course I do remember in the Methodist church I remember them having - well more or less we talk of it now as t
a
ble tennis but they always talked about it then days as - they had another name for it - but it was nearly table tennis, ping pong I believe it was. But it was just more or less table tennis. And may - remember a little of that played in the schoolroom of
 
the Methodist church on certain evenings. But that was about only thing in - that you would - well it's not exactly a ball game but it's the only thing nearest as that as I could think of because football was something that was never - didn't seem to take
 on at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No, cricket, no, in fact cricket is seldom talked about in Shetland at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not even today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You had books in the house didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes. We had books, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there a daily paper or weekly paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 
There was - there has always been a weekly paper right through to all my knowledge and that paper was nearly always - sought after but - very, very few, I cannot remember very many of the - what I call the mainland papers - coming. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 English or Scottish papers. There were very very seldom ever I seen much of them in my young days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have the Christian Herald?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That I have - yes, occasionally the like of the Christian Heralds did come and I remember once th
at I got up to maybe teenager or later on, maybe even later that, when I came back Shetland again I remember the likes of John Bull was very popular and - Answers was another paper. We used to go in for the - likes of - they had these little questions and
 that and also - I cannot remember first what come in then but they had questions - question and answer business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But that was when you returned to Shetland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I think that would have been when I returned to Shetland, I don't think I remember much about it before I left.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did any of the adults in the family read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, I - I never heard much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did all of you read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes, they were all able to read, oh yes, they'd all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I mean did they all read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well yes, of course I mean to say your question really should have a double meaning there because there was plenty of people at that stage that really wasn't able to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Of their generation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, there was a quite a few beca
use - you see, schools hadn't become - oh there was nothing compulsory about it, at that time. It was just - all my aunts and uncles and - well I don't know what my grandfather and grandmother - but my aunts and uncles had all gone to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But I suppose many of the older generation hadn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well I presume they wouldn't have done, if they went at all it was only just have been for a matter of a year or two and then they went away maybe to fishing or something in order to make a living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So I think they should bear that in mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well I think so, I think they could bear that in mind whether or not, I - I reckon there was very very few over the age of about twelve, by that time they was all looking for earning a living in some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  or form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Funeral? Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, oh yes. Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I wonder if you could describe a family funeral or how it was in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well in the count
ry districts it was usually funeral was - conducted in the home - in the house. And it was all by invitation, there wasn't any - public notice up. You were called by invitation and of course there was no undertakers out there, it was just - they were just
 
on - there were undertakers so far as making the coffin was concerned but beyond that - they did all their own laying out and suchlike. And - then the funeral was called to the house, or the party - funeral party was called to the house and - usually - ha
d
 your biggest room, or maybe best room, just depended, set out for this funeral company and you all sat down and the minister was there and a prayer as the case may be and - then the funeral left from there and it was all carried at that time. Long distan
ces in some cases, very long distances.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How far was it from your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well from our house it's just about close on ten miles. But in may cases it was quite a number of miles. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 In the far West of Walls, that's Dale of Walls which is some five mil
es from the village and they - there's a burn or - small stream that runs down through the - through the district and one side of that stream is Walls parish and the other side is Sandness parish. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 With the result that anyone on the far side of that stream 
was buried in Sandness. Well that was a terrible journey across this hill about three or four miles, easy that, and it was a terrible slow journey. Yes, carrying the coffin. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid860790\charrsid12791982 Many}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  times - heard peculiar stories told about that too you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Is it true that in the Walls area people used to take whisky and things along with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes. Oh yes. If they were - if they was carrying any distance there was always - whisky taken and there'd be one or two of the stances where they had to rest the - alway
s passed a lot around. Or - somebody take glasses. But that was always - it was - the fact of the matter, in this long distances it was - almost essential as a - way of refreshing - refreshment because - you know, it was even apart from carrying which was
 taken in turns but apart from that altogether it was a long walk through bad hilly district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did women ever go to the cemetery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, never. Never in these days at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember when your grandparents died whether you wore }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 mourning}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes, you always did. In the case of a - really youngster maybe what I say might have been my age, anything say from five 'til }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  or the like of that it was - you just didn't go into mournings exactly, you maybe had a black band or
 a black square sewed on your jacket. That was youngster but older - older people they went into mournings for maybe a couple of years. Oh yes. It was very long.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You didn't get new black clothes though when your grandparents died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not the likes of me, not in my - not a youngster like me but - the older ones always - oh yes, yes, that was essential.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about the custom of drawing the blinds, did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That was always done, oh yes, oh yes, the blinds was always down during the time of that the remains was in the house. Yes, yes, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When were the blinds lifted again then? After they'd gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Well immediately the remains was away from the house again and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 cort
\'e8ge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  left and the blinds was put up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If there was a death in a neighbour's house, would you draw your blinds for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well yes, if they was a very close neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not just for anybody in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. No, no. Oh no, not - not so far as that. Of course occasionally - I cannot remembe
r any special circumstance but I do know that occasionally it was the case that on the day of the funeral, when the funeral party was passing a house they might have drawn the blinds. Just while they were passing that house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
A little but not very much. I remember on one occasion in my very young days, I don't know what I would have been then, maybe about two or three year old I think, I remember my mother visiting a friend of hers, not
 very far away, just maybe about a couple of mile away. And I was with her. I - we must have been away for a week or a fortnight or something like that but in general I dinna remember me going a long way with folks very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about if they went visiting for an afternoon or an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You'd stay at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, they just went on their own. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Because there was always somebody to leave you with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, yes, there were always - there were plenty of people 
in the house, there's was always somebody and - in any case it was more or less they were just mixing with their own - their own age groups. And - it may have happened where there were children in the house, very occasionally, but I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 canna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  recall }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 special instance of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember a Bank Holiday being anything special at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh no, Bank Holidays were never heard of it. "Til I came away from - never heard of it until I came into town places, in the country of course there really was no banks of course }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 that}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  the result was there were no Bank Holidays recognised. The fact of the matter there was - to a certain extent - no holidays recognised at all. Unless maybe it was a Christmas or New }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 Years}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  Day and there was practically nothin
g else recognised in the way of holidays because - there wasn't very many people working for an employer, they were working for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And they had the animals to look after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And they had animals to look after and they just went out and did
 their daily work. Maybe at Christmas or a New Year or something like that they might have - just - well, made it more like a Sunday, just attended to the real necessities such as the animals and that and - and not bother just to go and dig in the croft o
r something of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But as far as going out for the day as people did in towns and things, there was nothing of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no. No, there was nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about going away for a holiday, that occasion when you went with your mot
her when you were very young, was that about the only time you went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
That's the only time that ever I recall that because generally speaking going away for holidays wasn't customary. It was - I mean holidays as we know them today just - just wasn't - didn't exist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did people ever come and stay with you and visit you and stop several nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I can never recall anybody doing that but there was - an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 occasion}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  which maybe worth nothing. You see, our - my - folks came from the island of Papa Stour really. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 
Well my grandfather did and my grandmother came from near Walls but they came from Papa Stour and they flit across to Sandness. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
They was nine years in Sandness and some my aunts was doing their schooling in Sandness before they came to W
alls. Now when the cattle sales was on, which by the way was a very very special day I can assure you, but when the cattle sales was on they had to swim these cattle out from Papa Stour. And they would stay then one night in Sandness. The next night they 
w
ould travel - around midday they would travel from Sandness to Walls which was six - six, no, maybe eight miles. They would travel them over to Walls and that particular case our house was particularly acceptable for staying the night in. Because our peop
l
e had belonged to Sandness and Papa Stour you see. And therefore I've seen a nothing - nothing unusual to see about anything from about a dozen to twenty cattle - tethered in our croft for the night and equal number of people attending them, some were get
ting down in the house, some were lying in the creatures and or maybe even stretched out and - having a bed on the floor or something like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 But}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  that was - oh it was quite an event I can assure you. I can remember that, I can remember all that cattle on
 our croft and the - all these folk stretched out on beds on the floor and this kind of thing. Oh it was quite an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 occasion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 .

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It must have been quite fun for a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It certainly was. It was - spent a good night. And of course the cattle sales there was - an important days. There was three I think }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 during}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 the year. There were three - three I think special days, Candlemass and Hallowmas and Lammas, I think that was the three sales, and I can assure you it was a big day that. The - the cattle sales ar
ound the Walls area was - was held at Bridge Walls which you would have passed on your way to Walls. And - they went away early - very early in the morning. There was no auction sales then, it was just a case of the buyers came along and they looked at th
e
 animals and they bought them, by independent bargain between the two. And - that went on - they would go very - well it was seven sales when daylight nearly all the time then, they might be away two or three o'clock in the morning and - by about midday t
h
en the selling part of it was all passed and then it was just a day then to - the young people dressed up and went there and right on the - right until teatime it was a just a crowd of young folk walking around from - for maybe a mile or so on each side a
nd meeting each other and having a bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 joke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 with each other and such like. Or maybe couples pairing off and were walking away. Then very very often you called at some house }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 before}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  you went home and a few more gradually gathered in some house which was in your route and you ended up maybe with somebody having a fiddle and you had a dance. So - it was really - that was really a big day I can }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 assure}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  you, the cattle sale day was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did the people stay on dancing until quite lat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh - o
h the dances that was held then a days it was a case of you never thought hardly of going home 'til more or less daylight. Oh yes. I remember on wedding I was at in Dale of Walls. And - you see Dale of Walls was a long way away, it was about five miles. A
nd it was almost the same time of day when I came back, that was twenty-four hours round from the time I'd left to go there. That was a wedding.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they have the custom around Walls of the gunner and the fiddler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well, no, I - I didn't - I cann
ot recall seeing that although I know it went on but I - I can never recall being connected with any of that much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But the wedding celebrations went on a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, you - you were - started off probably four or fiv
e o'clock in the afternoon and you were still on the floor at that time the next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. Definitely no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Could you read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You could - yes, you could have read, oh yes. But definitely no outside games or anything like that. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not even say chasing about with another lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, no, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were supposed to be quiet were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh reasonably so, you could have gone for a walk, with 
two or three chums maybe would go for a walk and like that but - try any kind of games or make any - noises or like of that, no, you was - they - frowned on that definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was only essential work done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Purely essential, just essential work only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No knitting or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, oh no, definitely not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have the custom of the Sunday clothes, especially for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Yes. Always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You said you went to the Methodist Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That is correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did all the others go to the Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, no there was - our family was - very mixed in that. There's some of them Church of Scotland, what they call the established church in these days, and there was some of them stood by that and some of them was Methodists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Have you any idea why they went to different }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 churches?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I could not say. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there in the Walls community more than just the Methodist and the Church of Scotland, were there other sects too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was. There was the Congregational and the United }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 Free}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Four churches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was four }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 churches}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you say that there were any difference in the class of type of person that went to the different churches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No - I reckon there was a spattering
 of both classes at all the churches. There was the same sort of class distinction was - was noticeable but - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 church alike. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have Sunday school outings in those days, treats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. We had - at least one Sunday school picnic eac
h year. Oh you couldn't go very far I mean the - a very - very often you went by boat maybe to Vaila, the island of Vaila. I remember that on more than occasion going in a big boat; what we called a sixern. That was the bigger, the six rowing boat, bigger
 - bigger than the normal rowing boat that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 you would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 see here or sailing boat you would see here round Lerwick, it was bigger than that and you - you, oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 practically}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 fill that boat and go to maybe anything up to about thirty or forty of you going out to Vaila.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any other clubs or activities organised in connection with your church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not at that time, no. No, there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there no temperance club?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 A choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Yes, there was a choir always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. I never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did everybody in the family attend some place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, I think they did as far as I can
 remember, they all - of course some of them was getting - when my memory goes back to there were some of them getting to the stage like my grandfather and grandmother and that that they - they was more or less past that, it meant a fairly long walk you s
ee and - but my aunts anyways and my uncle, well my one uncle with the wooden leg, I don't - I can - canna recall him going but - all the others went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the Walls community was there a sort of social pressure to attend some church or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, t
here definitely was. I think that I can - as far as I can recall the - anyone as didn't go to church - they were sort of been frowned on if they didn't have a - a special reason for it like as I say there was my - some people getting too old for that and 
- anybody with any defect or disease that they couldn't get to that way. But - there was a lot more visiting by the ministers in them days. Very much more than what is nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was it just the Methodist minister who would visit Methodists and that type of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 More or less, yes, I - I never remember them going to the other - other religions, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was your house visited then by the Church of Scotland and the Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. It was - they were, yes. And I somehow recall mostly Methodist.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember your uncle taking an interest in politics when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much. Politics, I can't remember politics hardly ever being discussed in our family at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you have any idea what your uncle's views were on the politics. Parties or the state of the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well - of course the - as it is today the Liberals are very - strong through Shetland I think. For more or less most of my lifetime, it's still of course - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  is pretty well - in the forefront here yet. And I've a feeling that - as far as politics was concerned that the Liberal had fairly strong - there was a fairly strong leaning to Liberalism right through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Through your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, I - I think if there was anything, I never remember much politics talked about, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But you think they probably were Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I - I - I'm inclined to think that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember any of the family voting at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I - no, I can't recall - I can't just specify any particular occas
ion that I ever noted - noted any of them going to a polling station. But no doubt they did but I just can't recall that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there much sort of political excitement around Walls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There weren't sort of great troops of children going round shouting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, no, very very little of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you ever hear of any man feeling himself under any pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, never. I never heard of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I wonder if it ever did happen - employers or landlords?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I don't think so, I don't - don't think it - well I couldn't recall ever knowing it. No, I never heard about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did the womenfolk in the house have any interests outside the home, they went to church, did they belong to any Guilds or organisations?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, there wasn't much of that kind to belong to. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 
There was very, very little in the - even in the church, I can't recall any Guilds or anything of that kind, they would have - certain concerts or soirees they called it whic
h was really a hectic arrangement apparently to my way of thinking for the - for the church because a pretty righteous sometimes but they would have these soirees and they would have concerts in the church, but I cannot recall any sort of - fellowship of 
any kind such as a Gild or - nothing like that kind.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
