\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 school age}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 After school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. That more
 or less every evening you went out and - unless the weather was just too bad or something but otherwise you went out and you just - few of you would meet and join up together and be at somebody's house. I don't know what they call it or not but - in norm
a
l. Another thing that we notice today is - all the - people around the place or anybody needed help of any kind, it didn't matter what it was, help, say they were behind with their croft work or something like that, the rest of the crowd around would gath
e
r and help them and - and they would have been insulted if you had said pay. Oh no, no, no, no. They would take it as an insult. You see you don't get that kind of thing today. I mean, it wouldn't matter - well you might get it in a very very small scale 
b
ut generally speaking if you say to somebody - or - well they don't - they don't volunteer but if you had say to somebody well, I'd like some little thing done, well - you would never dream of asking them to do it without asking for pay. What the charge w
