 it with a scythe. But now this last couple of years since }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  was a chap that came next door to us here,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982  he\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  a schoolteacher really, and he - he's on
e of this kind who - mows and he'll come across two or three times during the seasoned cut the grass and of course he would never dream of getting any pay for it. That's just a - that's just sort of a - a sample of them giving you what - still can happen 
but - that's not general. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Unfortunate really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It seems to be, I'm nearly inclined to agree with you, it is unfortunate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was your uncle generally at home in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there anything like a pub or club that menfolk went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No. No. I - I do remember - there was a pub, yes, there was a pub at Bridge Walls And - there was - the few but not very many that - bothered to go there of the evening. And unfortunately it wasn't the case of they went there 
was just to maybe have a glass of beer and sit over it for the, quite of the night. It was a case of if you went there at all nine case out of ten they got - they got - over the wind before they came out again. But - with the result that they couldn't jus
t
 make a practice of that. It wasn't like what your - well, even in Lerwick here I mean there are plenty of people - although I don't suggest - agree with it - I'm not a teetotaler or anything of that kind but I mean I - I canna get away just going and sit
t
ing in a pub for most of the night. I canna get away with that somehow. It didn't appeal to me. That's not to say I'm not a strict teetotaler or anything, it's not a case that I have any objections to a drink or anybody having a drink in moderation but - 
there - sit in a pub I - I couldn't do it. I couldn't do it somehow or other, it - jars on me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your uncle ever go to this pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I - no, he never did. The uncle that I mainly stayed with never went but I remember my other uncle was finally
 - well he was - yes, he was - he was in the house right enough. At times because I tell you I think he was - I - he was more or less engaged in - maybe away from home as a ploughman. But I remember when he was at home he was one of the crowd that used to
 
go there occasionally and generally it was to his disadvantage because generally he come roaring home again. And a peculiar thing I'll tell you. I was very young and I remember me being very young about then, at the most I must may be only three or four y
e
ar old. And he was - he was in a nasty temper when he got drunk too, as affects some people that way. And - if he - generally he was singing - he was coming home singing and he dome home, if they - they would hear him singing maybe on a fine night as he's
 coming home. And if they wanted him to come in and be nice and quiet I was sent out to meet him. And he would pick me up and come in as quiet as a lamb. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I don't think you mentioned that uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I - the - that's why I didn't mention him 
as being a regular member of the household but - he was home occasionally and - I know it was - I mean, I can recall there's me having to go and meet him when he was have a drop of drink and - likewise I remember me being at his wedding. He married - the 
m
aid out of the - what was probably the most important house in Shetland - in Walls - in Walls, that was the Post Office and - Springfield as they called it. And she was - she had been the maid there for many years and so the wedding, the reception was hel
d in the Springfield house you see. And - I remember me at the wedding for almost a week. I don't know what I would have been maybe - och, maybe about seven or eight year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The people that kept the Post Office was that a sort of shop too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was, yes, oh yes, it was grocers shop and - and Post Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they the most well-to-do shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well I should say they were, yes. You know - people would today, I've told once or twice and I think they hardly - scarcely believe me. When I
 was clerk in the steamers office, steamers store, in Walls, we were supplying twenty-four shops round this - store in Walls. Admittedly there was - one - one or two of that shops that was almost half way to Lerwick but - inside the village of Walls, the 
perimeter of the village of Walls there was eleven shops. And today - today there's one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  shops in Lerwick then in those days, there seems to me to be very few shops in Lerwick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I don't think there was any more in Lerwick, no, bec
ause you see the - that has been a very special characteristic or feature of the - of Shetland in general, mind I don't think Shetland would have been in particular because - I think it's been throughout the whole of Scotland, is - they've gathered from t
h
e country to the town. With the result that - see the first thing that began to kill the little country shop was the rents. Vans coming out from Lerwick, you see, that's what - the; first move in killing the - well, maybe not just the first because the po
pulation began to go down and people began to find work around }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 Lerwick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
-, that was maybe the very first but generally speaking what killed the country shop was the vans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember roughly when that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well there was a tremendous chan
ge in the ten year or so that I was - in the Merchant Navy, there was a tremendous change during that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It started }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 really}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  during the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It - during the first world war and right on 'til about the - well the fact of the matter t
hat was the - the drift began then and during the first world war and that just continued right up to the present day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did anyone in the family belong to savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. No. I never heard much about that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you know if they paid into a doctor's fund, a health fund of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. Oh no. No, doctor's - doctor's fees was just paid as they were - as you needed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Where was the doctor then, was there on in Walls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was one at Bridge Walls. Which was abo
ut two miles from our house. And I knew very well about it because I was - I was fairly sickly in my young days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were often sick were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was, I had - it might be an interesting story too because - from - from seven - from I was seven to 
eleven, I was a matter with bronchitis. And the doctor took me into his care, he was a very - rough I can assure you, he was very much inclined to drink and all the rest of it but nevertheless he was a good doctor. And he took a great interest in me and -
 
when I was eleven year old then he gave our people a prescription and he says, you - you can keep this 'til he's twenty-one and if he doesn't need it 'til he's twenty-one, he says, you can chuck it in the fire. And I've never bothered with it since. And h
e told me then, he told me, told our people when he finished with he says, when I started with him, he said, there was spots the size of a penny on his lung. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 
And - that was - there was no sanitoriums or anything of that kind then days you know and - right enough I mean to say I never hardly develop a cough or nothing else right up to the present day. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And he just cured - he just kept that four years, he just kept steady on, mind me, the fact of the matter was cod - cod liver oil came to me as I've been drinking it the same as you would take a glass of milk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You used to have a lot of it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes, quite a lot. But I was - which meant that I would - naturally quite a lot away from school too. Not in long spells but - days now and again you know like I couldn't make it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any races round Walls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Dog racing, horse racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. Nothing like that, only - only the one particular day when you got - you didn't get anything of that kind but you get individual 
races just to - such as children running and that kind of thing, you got that on the regatta day. That was a big day you know. Oh yes. That was - nowadays it's drifted down to practically nothing except just boating, sailing races and that but once upon a
 time that was a big day I can assure you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That was what time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I think it would have been roughly around - or maybe it would have been about this time of year or maybe slightly - might be later than this because - I - have visions tha
t there were a good part of the crop gathered in by that time. Which would have been later than this but still - couldn't have been very much later because I know the weather was generally pretty good. So I would say it would have been around - around abo
ut the - August period. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Who were the children that you played with as a child, were they neighbour's children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 More or less yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any other children quite close to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very close, no. There was - our 
house - here was two houses situated quite close to each other and the one hill dyke as you would say, one dyke covered two crofts you see with just a small division right down the middle. And in that house there was no children, the other house. So my - 
w
ell in fact my nearest - children that I had to play with was - oh about five minutes walk away and was from the area where I ended up to that my wife came from. That was about the nearest family more or less to us. But it was easy - five minutes walk or 
more from the house. See there was only that two houses really close together just at that one particular point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not when I was a child. There was no actual policeman in Walls but - I think I re
member a - in my teenage days there was - there was a policeman stationed for a short time in Walls. I know there was one and I don't remember an awful lot about him so maybe - it might have been during the time that went away from Walls just while he was
 there because I know - I know he was there and I remember a little about him but somehow I didn't seem to remember others being there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How did he treat the people, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I don't think he bothered very much at all. I think the sort time - he wasn't worrying very much about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 He wasn't always around the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. No, no, no. He wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you ever told by grown ups, if you don't do such and such a thing I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, well - of course they couldn't
 very well say they'd call a policeman because the policeman wasn't there to call but - they always tried to have some kind of bogey that they frighten you with you know but - but the policeman at there was - and I never hardly remember that happening in 
my young days. If there was anything really serious then the police was called from Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You paid rent for your home to Anderton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What was he like as a landlord, did he look after the property at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, 'course }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  - they never - they never did anything of that kind, you did that on your own. Of course, mind you, the rent was insignificant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did he do anything for the people in the way of, say very poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not to my knowledge, no, I never remember
 that. He was a good enough landlord, he wasn't a - there was nothing - or nothing - unfair about him but I mean he just kept his peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What difference did it make to the family when the breadwinner was ill or out of work, that sort of thing didn't really apply did it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, it didn't, no, not very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there ever during that period when you were still at home say up to 1913 any period when you were in want in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I can never recall that, no. Things might have been tig
ht but never - never to - have really - we never went short of anything. Not necessities of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you aware of a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not - very much, just - it was - noticeable that everybody had to be - to pull their weight so to speak. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 
But outside of that I never saw anything just - I never sort of having to make any special - special effort outside the normal working day which of course - knitting was very, very prominent, I mean, people - every - every woman had her knitting and 
of course all knitting was taken right from you to you as you would say, from ewe to you, right from the - from the sheep\rquote s back right to the knitted garment was all processed through - at home.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was spun in the home in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Carded and spun and all that at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you pluck your sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They weren't sheared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, well you see the Shetland sheep, it was no use trying to shear the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 
Shetland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  - the real Shetland sheep, that's something that I've had very
 often to explain in my association with the exhibition - is - there's a great difference. The Shetland sheep you didn't need to shear for the simple reason because if you didn't pluck it off it came off itself. Whereas today there is not very many real S
hetland sheep, they're nearly - nearly all of them have a little bit of cross in them and you notice you must pluck because you would never - you tear the skin if you try to pull the wool out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you help in that as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you ever remember being made to leave the district by rough music, that is banging tin cans to make a loud noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. Oh no. No. Oh no. Oh no, that never - never applied at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It used to happen on rare occasions in England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Maybe so but I never - never in Shetland, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady when you were a teenager or a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I wouldn't say that we do. There was the sort of class distinction, there was
 the - a certain group but - associated with each other while one class of slightly better standard and other but outward, no, not a real gentleman, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The term wasn't used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, it wasn't used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you brought up to touch your cap or touch your forelock or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. No, it didn't happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did women curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not to my knowledge, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were telling me you played with the children about five minute's walk away, whereabouts did you play, did you play
 indoors or outdoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Depending on the type of weather, if it was - you were playing out of doors if it was decent weather. A croft lent itself very much to that because - I mean you had a big space and - again there was - I can always recall lots of
 - yards you know, some for cabbages and others for just growing the - the cabbage plants and suchlike and there was always a lot of that and it was - just the very type of thing that kids would amuse themselves in you see, playing hide and seek or anythi
ng of that kind you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It must have been ideal for children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember if you were allowed to play with any children in the neighbourhood that you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I think so, I don't - don't remember any distinction there.
 Oh of course there was the same thing would have applied - well we were - our house was a bit away from the centre where shops and all that was - but - in that area I have a feeling that there was a certain amount of distinction as regards the better cla
ss or so called better class children. They maybe didn't just - completely keep themself to themself and - of course there was always - they were all quite free at a school. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 I reckon}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  in their play hours outside school, they would have been more or less,
 they would have played on their own, they maybe wouldn't just have been warned to do that but I think it was - sort of came naturally. They mixed in when - with their own class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any families who were considered undesirable by your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, there were not. I couldn't - I couldn't recall anything of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So the society around Walls was broadly in two classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you say that there was much variation in the standard of living or standard of comfort and general attitudes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, quite a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Within your class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes, yes, there was quite a bit and between - between the two classes there was quite different standard of living, the - I mean the household arrangements and - I presume to 
a certain extent the class of food that they eat too. Was - more sophisticated as I would call it, it wasn't maybe so rough as what we had more the rougher kind that was nearly all - say your own baking and - maybe quite a lot of oatmeal and stuff of that
 kind, whereas they would probably be quite a lot more of the bought and tinned. Well there wasn't so much tinned stuff then but - it was bought stuff.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Taking the majority of the people, was there much variation within say the working class or poorer class or whatever you like to call it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were slightly better off were you than quite a lot of families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I would think we would have been - maybe it was just a case that I was brought up among all older people. There w
asn't a lot of other children to feed, there may have been something in that but - I think the general standard of living among the particular class - I don't think there'd have been great deal of difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there cotters there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was 
a few. Not very many. Cotters, as I remember them, there was one or two of them that was in pretty dire straits. You did get then I think what's - thank goodness you don't get now and that was a few who were having to go begging. I do remember that, yes. 
But - not to a great extent and it was practically dying out by the time that I come to remember but there was - I still can remember - one or two that was at that stage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they elderly or were they younger people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, they were elderly. Yes. I think they probably just - I think the natural }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4547181\charrsid12791982 occurrence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  would have been that when these people passed on then they would - there wouldn't have been any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In what manner did they beg, did they come around to the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They just come aro
und to the houses and people - well - generally speaking they didn't have to beg, they didn't - people just realized who they were and - and what state they were in and the result was just more or less gave them - always something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they ever invited in to have a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes, they - they were never looked down on, there was never - I mean, although people would have known that they were - at the begging stage but they would never have let - let them see that. Well I - as far 
as our house was concerned anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So they didn't have less respect for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, no. No, no. They didn't - they didn't make any show of it at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 As far as playing with other children was concerned there were no children that your par
ents thought were rough or ill mannered that you shouldn't play with or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, I don't think - I can never recall that, no. I might have had my own obsessions about somebody that - or - better keep clear of him, he's a pretty rough c
haracter or something like that or - not for - that might just have been on my own so to speak but never came to the extent that your parents was on your guard, never thought that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What was their attitude to getting your clothes dirty when you played, was a fuss made about that or didn't that matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh they - generally a pretty bit of a fuss made about that. You generally got the rough side of the tongue or maybe they - I never remember much else but you generally got a pretty good telling o
ff when that happened. I can remember when - little story, it might be interesting. Close by our house there was a little stream that ran you see. And - in summer it practically dried up but in winter it was fairly heavy burn. And - naturally between the 
t
wo periods would be just a mass of mud and suchlike. And there was - there was a bridge that went across there - oh maybe about this width of a bridge you see, and close by that there were two fairly high banks or it wasn't high, it was - in a way - maybe
 
about so high you see, but it was high for me, I was only a wee toddler about two or three year old. And apparently I dropped in here over those banks and I actually got out on my own but I was in a fair - bonny old mess when I got out. And so some - some
 of the folk asked me well who did I get out? Oh, I says, I - I did what I could and then the good man did the rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you go fishing as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I never went very much fishing. I remember me going as - maybe as a teenager poaching. Which was
 going with a net at night and - and a gas lamp and - finding - the trout in the burns and scooping them up with a net you know. But that had to be done at night so that - there was - well there wasn't plenty of people but there was the occasional one and
 - look out for you because that was poaching and that; wasn't - wasn't lawful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was that the Laird's rights to have that? Who had the rights to the fish then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh well, I don't know, there was nobody particular but there was the - the like of a gr
ound officer or somebody that had a little bit of law on their side, they would very often if there was - if they had a strict nature they would be on the look out for you and - if they did catch you, well, probably they would report you high - higher up.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would that be the factor too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, the - the factor - the factor would have been inclined to do the same thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Because it belonged to the Anderton family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well it would have yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Naturally it would. Ay}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about walking, going for walks, for the sake of pleasure of walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Aye. Well there wouldn't have been much of that - engaged in unless maybe on a Sunday or something, just passing time, to pass the time on a Sunday. And you would maybe go for a walk but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I did - well, now, yes, as a teenager, immediately - just about the time that I started on work then my step-father gave me a bike. And - I always remember that bike because it was specially spring bike, it had double - double fram
e, because most bikes were just single frame. Double - double tubing. And I had - so I was one of the very earliest ones that had bikes there, oh yes. Of course you know I thought I was somebody when I got a job because the - jobs under an employer were j
ust a thing almost unheard of, there was so very little of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 A lot of unemployment was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well there wasn't much unemployment but they were always - they were just engaged round their own croft and suchlike but get work outside of the home and - under an employer and - just at a specified job - you thought yourself somebody then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was just the case that the chap before me had left and I made application for it and got it, I - I forget if there was anybo
dy else but myself but I'm not too sure of that. But I got the job and I can assure you I was a proud man and my wages at that time was four shillings a week. Four shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How much of that did you keep for yourself when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh
 well I think I used to keep the whole thing, I don't think anybody - no, I don't think they ever asked me for anything. Unless I wanted to maybe want to put a shilling or two fast and maybe buy myself anything in the line of clothes or that, I don't know
 they would never ask me for anything about housekeeping or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What were your hours in that first job you had?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - I cannot recall - I think it would be roughly about - nine to either four or five. It would be either a seven or eight hour day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Saturdays too, or half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No Saturday was - Saturday was just the same as any other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No there was nothing talked about Saturday then. But - I can just somehow recall it would have been probably a seven or
 eight hour days. And - I always - we had an hour for dinner, I got - I used to get my dinner at the - I didn't go right up to our home because that was too far away but - I got my dinner beside friends in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you pay them for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, I cannot ever remember paying them, I think that our folk occasionally maybe gave them something in the line of groceries or that for it but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That links up with what you were saying earlier doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. That - just about, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In that job there was just one other man was there in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There was just - agent - steamer's agent, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was he there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, he wasn't there all the time, he was - well in the latter part when things was beginning to get a 
bit slack as I told you before that the steamers began to gradually - go maybe two weeks and three weeks between, then that people also had had a shop. A grocers shop and they bought hosiery as well. And if he felt that things was just wasn't very busy do
wn around the store then he would go and help the missus in the shop and leave the whole thing to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So you were sometimes quite alone there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Unsupervised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Unsupervised.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What sort of man was he to work with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh very nice. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Oh very, very nice, yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about the work itself, how did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Oh I was very, very happy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You enjoyed the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, I've always enjoyed the work. All kinds of work. I - I've been every; blink
ing thing I think and then some. I've had - I'll not blow any fuss about that but I've been - and I was at sea until I was sailing second officer and - I - was in what they called the road department in charge of about five hundred men and - also at the l
ower end of the scale again I even attended the public toilets for a while. Every blinking thing - every job. But I'll say one thing - besides that, I was never longer than a week out of work ever in my life. From I was fourteen until my present day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That must be quite unusual really?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 That is, and I'm very, very pleased and thankful to say that I've never had one penny either out of off the dole nor from the health. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I'm very pleased to say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Thinking back to that job was that the first pay or money that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You didn't have a job while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. No, no. Not a paid job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It wasn't the custom round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, it wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How long were you at that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was - three year - well around - around about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well I had to keep a check of all the goods going out of the - the actual manifest - big sheet which came with the boat and a list of the goods that was m
ore or less handled by the agent himself but - the gook was kept and everything as went out of that store and which was taken away - of course not by lorry but by cart then, and everything that was taken away by cart or by small boat then that had to be c
hecked in that small book - in that little book and compared with the - with the main sheet that came from the steamer. And had to tally out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were they particular about neatness of figures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, well I never heard any complaint, that's all I can say, I never heard any complaint about figures. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was after you left that job that you went into the Merchant Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's correct. That is correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That was 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And you went away then and your home then was in South Shields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well after a bit, you see, the first ship that I had - was the - the two ships that I had was both sailing from Shetland here. And the first one was torpedoed and we lost here and then went in another one which took her place. And -
 that one was taken off government service and put in her place you see. And we went - me and the other Crane boys - it was Crane boys then, men drives the cranes nowadays but we drove the cranes you see. That was before you - that was the first step and 
t
hen you became ordinary seamen you see. And - me and the other crane boy, we were transferred to the new - the other boat when she came along and - I was on her, well - I couldn't say, roughly it would have been - well I - I still - I still had been - I w
as out on the shipping boats before the war finished, I remember that much but I just can't remember dates. I - well I could look it up but I don't want the trouble of it, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But roughly it was about 181 or '19 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 About 18 - well it was the twelfth - it was the 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 of February 1918 that we were torpedoed and then I joined the other ship, well that was in February and I - oh I probably was about six months on her. And after that then - I was on ships which wasn't coming back and forth t
o Shetland with a result I started to make my home in Shields after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And you carried on in the Merchant Navy until you returned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That is - 'til I returned to Shetland.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 With all the tragedies in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That is correct. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember the date?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
When I came home? It was in 1927 but - I cannot just recall, it was - it must have been round about October or November. It was 1927 anyway. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You had reached the rank of second officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Aye, the rank of
 second officer although I never had any tickets or anything of that kind but it was in the days of the - tickets wasn't very much looked for. It was mainsailing skipper didn't have a ticket. In the smaller vessels of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Then they found you a job with the County Council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That's correct, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you start off working on the roads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I did work - pick and shovel work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And can you carry on from them?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I had - I was about maybe two years in that and then I was made road
 foreman, what you might call ganger, which meant that I had about three or four men under me and - from that there was a new surveyor that came to Shetland and - road surveyor. And he had this idea of supervisory foreman. And there was - I understand, I 
- I don't know who they all were but there was - I believe there was fourteen that got the chance to apply. And out of that fourteen I seemed to be chosen and that meant I had to shift out of Walls. And - I first was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Gow,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  Lerwick where - that's close by Lerwick, I was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Cowlick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  for about six months along with my half brother which was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Gow,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 Lerwick then and - and I handled Lerwick, Scalloway and south to Sumburgh. That part. Then I - but after six month I got a house in Sandwick, I got the two or three
 rooms in Sandwick and got down there. And roughly about that time, well maybe I'm just forgetting exactly bit it was that time but - on the one occasion the surveyor remember we was going to Burra Isle together and the chap that had been on the other par
t
 of Shetland he had been put inspector on the tar macadam work which was starting then in Shetland, it was the first of if you see, and he put inspector on that. And the surveyor was going away, on holiday or something like that, and he passed this remark
 
to me he says, I don't know, he says, what's going to happen when I go away, he says, the whole north end of Shetland's going to be unattended. And he left the - I don't know what the - what he was aiming at but at least he should hade - waited for a whil
e
 for this to sink in so to speak and then after a bit he said, do you think you could manage the whole lot and - sort of smiles and said, well I - it's seems a pretty big undertaking but - I'll tell you what, I'll try it for the month that you're away, I 
s
ays, and if - sort of all well and good and if not, he says, I'm quite prepared to go back on my Lerwick, Scalloway and Sumburgh. I says, I want to go back there, I says, I dinna want to be put in any other place. Oh yes, this was a guarantee. And of cour
se I ended up with being - having the whole lot for twelve years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Five hundred men was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well there were - for a time there were five hundred men, during the war period there was five hundred, well roughly you know. About five hundred men beca
use you see the two aerodromes was both being constructed. And I reckon there were easy maybe a hundred and forty men on each of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What year was it that you left working for the council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was - it would have been - '55. 1955 because I was almost exactly thirty year with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And you decided to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I decided to go in for public house contracting on my own which was a very silly thing, but still, you do many silly things with your life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You weren't able to make that pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No. It was - a great - a tremendous amount of our work was with the hydroelectric board. Doing all the smaller jobs which the big contractor passed and he - the big contractor was then installing electricity through Shetland. And - many times when the
y had passed somebody didn't take the electricity. Well later on they decided they would take it and the result was that probably you'd three or four poles to put up and suchlike and - these was - we did an awful lot of that kind of work with the hydroboa
r
d. And then the hydroboard after a few years started take an direct labour. And they had been our best customers by all means, there was more than half our work had been for them. And gradually it just began to quieten down with them and they took direct 
labour and - the result was that it really wasn't worth working with. So then I went in for agencies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you were doing the contracting how many men did you have working for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I had sometimes between twenty and thirty men working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And then you went in for agencies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I went in for agencies, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did that mean traveling for different firms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was, yes, traveling for different firms and - and I - several agencies at one time you see and some of them was maybe dealing with 
- with the retailers and others would be dealing with the general public.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What exactly did you have to do in this work, you had to travel around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh you traveled - I traveled through the whole of Shetland, and even Orkney in some cases I went do
wn to Orkney. And did travel in Orkney too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were saying it was very tiring, did you have to do a lot on your feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Ah yes, well you see, when I - it was all right for a while and I had - I had various agencies such as electric light bulbs an
d - that was just one of them and - and mats and various things like that, that I had from different firms and that time it was all right because - I was always using a car and just getting - didn't have very much maybe to carry with me. Maybe just a - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 attach\'e9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 case or something like that. But when it came to a case of I went in metal ware and brush firms and that kind of thing then two big - maybe one huge case and - and that - well occasionally you got your car right to the door but on the other hand again
 you maybe had to go a bit of traveling. It's come a little bit you much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So when did you give that up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well I gave - it was just gradually that dropped down and I had various jobs, for instance as I was telling you I was even down the toilets f
or a while at the toilet in the - the public toilets there, night - night time. And also I - in the fact of the matter one time I was trying to do three jobs, I - there was quarry at the - suddenly - the chap that was - had been looking after the Ministry
 
of Labour Exchange and he was suddenly taken to hospital and they were absolutely stuck and finally when one of them landed on me and got me to come and take that part and at the same time I was - trying to - do a job looking after the - the playing parks
 
here at night and I took on the toilets as well so I had as well - so I had the three jobs all at the one time. They were all different places but got the final - sort of got them all to work in - to work in with one another you see. So I had the three fo
r a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 The private contracting was for how many years roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I should say roughly about five - six years. Five or six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You gave it up about 1960?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Round about that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And then you went into the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982  agency}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Went in agencies, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When did you stop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well of course that I mean that in that I - yes, well I suppose that's almost right because - I've been seven year in this church job and I more or less dropped the agencies then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were carrying on a bit of the agency work while you were doing the caretaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes, yes, I was doing - still doing a little of that. But - it wasna - I - I was giving up the humping around big heavy cases I mean to say it was just a case of maybe acting for - f
or a firm's car like, it had nothing to do with carrying around a - a file or something that with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What is your present work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Church officer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And what does that entail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 That entails - looking after the church and the church hall. And likewise - attending any weddings or funerals and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You have to be there do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So you've had a great variety of jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I have done. No, I've never been a gravedigger, no, I've never tried that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you
 have preferred another type of occupation, was there any particular sort of work which you had a hankering for but which you've never done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I don't think there was. I generally - well I've been - I think the best way to answer that is to say tha
t I've been happy in every job I went to. I've never been dissatisfied. And I've always what I would say in my opinion got a fair deal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 
I've been very, very much - I thing which - I think is maybe helped very - a lot and that is I've been very, very much on my own, nearly in every job I've gone into I haven been - had very much strict supervision. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It wasn't very long - I mean this maybe - I don't like to say it because it looks maybe like - sort of blowing me own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 horn as you'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  say but in most cases somehow they must have realized that I could be left to work on my own sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You could be trusted to get on with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Fair - fairly so because nearly - practically every - line I've tried and again I - I'm not trying to blow my own horn but bec
ause I can sort of prove it, I've generally progressed as far as I could get unless I had had certificates and tickets and etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you ever serve an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 apprenticeship}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  or training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Never. Never in any of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I have - I'm - I'm a trade union rebel. I'm completely adverse - adverse to trade unions. I am absolutely in every way. Since the time - since I went to join one ship and I was refused because I wasn't a gra
de union and I'm - I - from that day and on I then said to my - thought to myself well, if I'm going to lose my livelihood simply because I'm not in a trade union then the trade union is no use to me, and I've been a trade union rebel ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You never joined one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I never have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or that they were in conflict in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, well - difficult to say - there, because I always found that if you - played the game and did you
r best that - an employer did likewise. That's the way I found. Other people seems to have found it other ways but I have never found it other way. In all jobs where I have been - I have never been a stickler for hours or anything of that kind I mean, and
 
- when I was in the roads department it didn't matter two hoots to me, if I started a job that had to be done if I should have been working to midnight it never worried me. And when I was - at the supervisory foreman stage well I was on a weekly wage and 
I wasn't on hourly rate and the result was it didn't matter two hoots to me, I just carried on, the job had to be done did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Which is not really a trade union attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It's - no, it's no - they wouldn't - they wouldn't fall in with that at all
 but nevertheless it - I think it - I think it was appreciated and that was why - I probably got advancement.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In those days, before 1918, would you say there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, there was - in f
act of the matter there wasn't - there wasn't a lot of trained - what you would call - there was very few that had served an apprenticeship. They may have - well let us say they'd been - had happened to be working along with a - a man who knew his job and
 there - they by became a skilled man at his job bus as regards tradesman - serving an apprenticeship, well that just a thing that just wasn't known. In my early days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In your early days did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, not in - not in my early days. There was - there too much - there was so much of the help one another so to speak that you couldn't - you couldn't hardly get a division of interest. You couldn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you say full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, I don't know, not changed my attitude to life, I think what did change my attitude to life more than anything else was my - Merchant Navy experience. Definitely that changed my attitude becaus
e - it put me out among strangers and I - saw the world and I sailed the - with all various kinds of people and - the parts as I say from seeing the world and being in foreign countries and being amongst strangers and living among strangers, living in Eng
land rather than Shetland, all these kind of things definitely, there's no question about it, that had a - that had a particular ruling on my life afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you say in what particular ways it altered you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well it altered me in such a way I'
m sure that - I don't feel anyways embarrassed in working with - strangers or with any other body. For one thing I've never even - although there is that very slight - very slight, I know it is very slight but there is still that very slight social distin
c
tion or social feeling even today in the church circles. But I never - I never pay any attention to that. I just - whether it's man or woman, it doesn't matter to me, I mean I just speak to them the same as we're sitting speaking now, I never pay any atte
n
tion to the fact that they were maybe well think themselves just a slight or wee bit - it's not nearly so much as used to be but they still think themselves maybe a little bit just - wee thing you see. But - and I think that my experience - especially in 
going out among folk elsewhere is led to that, that I - never feel the slightest bit embarrassment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you say that Shetland people who haven't been out of Shetland would feel more embarrassed then you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There is, there definitely is. Yes. The
re definitely is, yes. And there is the certain type of people that goes for Shetland that I dinna think they - I mean they dinna - change so much, they dinna - maybe they don't pick up so much of the - style in other parts of the world, I think maybe I'v
e been - my nature has led me to - to adapting more to this - to other peoples.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Some people never really change, they always long for their old country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, and the - and they - I - I - I notice it very much even in people that's coming here, we
ll I have a - I have a great interest you know in meeting people, I really - I do have an interest that I've been - what for three year - for three year past I've been chairman of the exhibition here, the summer exhibition here at Ellsbrough House and I t
hink the only thing that does tempt me to go there where I've attended to it for maybe twenty years now, nearly all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 time I've been in Lerwick I've been doing something about it, this past three year I've been chairman of it and - the main thing that att
racts me there is the amount of strangers you meet, and you can yarn with them and you can get all shades of opinion and I - I feel - I feel very much at home there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It's stimulating too isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Definitely. And - most of the people - of course
 it's all voluntary and most of the people that comes and attends that exhibition - as - stewards as you would say and - we have the - the team that doing knitting and spinning and carding and all that kind of thing, the womenfolks and - and showing off t
h
e hosiery and we have like a big craftroom where crafts is and fishing and agriculture, all that, and we have the different people from each of that sections and the - I think they all come there for the same thing, the only - the people that comes there 
is the people who is interested in meeting other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Thinking back to when you were a clerk, did your life change in any way after you left school, did you continue to go to Sunday school for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, not so much, no. No, I think it reall
y - I canna remember me ever taking much part in - in Sunday school - Sunday - Sunday school or - or even church. Not much after I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did starting full time work change your relationships with your relations in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. Oh no. Oh no, I think that - I don't think that happened at all. Just went on as usual.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Can you think of any changes, the sort of people you associated with for example until you went to see, were they the same as you'd known when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They were the same, the same - the same chums that had grown up to be about my own age and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 In fact the matter strange to say there's - there's three of us was sort of bosom pals about that time and - one of them is in - stayed in South Shields, been
 there for many, many years and he comes up he says, he's in Shetland in Lerwick just now, he comes up every year now - for about the last four or five years he - he hadn't been home for oh maybe twenty - thirty year and then he come up to attend the - hi
s sister's golden wedding. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
And - ever since that he's come up every year and he's up just now and - and other one of the three bosom pals is out at Walls and - we meet just the same today as we were when we were - were when we were twelve year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You're very lucky to keep them like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did your family meet your friends, they would have known them I suppose because I imagine everyone knew everyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes, all the likes of Walls you knew everybody. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you went out in the evening did they like to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, they definitely did. They liked to know where you were, oh very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So if you said you were going out would they sort of ask you what you'd be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, they - they wouldn't maybe have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 interfered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 with what you were doing but they would like to known where you were and another thing you can realized this was isolated district, country, districts. And - up 'til - especially up 'til you left the school well they had to
 be careful about where you were because otherwise - might come on bad weather or anything, snow or let's say snow or gale wind or anything and - and if they knew where you - they nearly had to know where you were or else you might never have got home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
So when you gathered round the Post Office or went to another person's house would you always know in advance which house you were going to be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, no, of course that would have been - that's when you come to your teenage stage and then peopl
e wasn't interfering very much about where you were going. On no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You mean it was just in the immediate years or two after leaving school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Yes, well but - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What age was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Once that you left school, once that you were about maybe fifteen years of age as a lad I don't - I never mind them bothering much about }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 where you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  went. You just went out on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But at around thirteen or fourteen would they expect to know then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - they maybe would but not after that. No later than that anyway. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was more during your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 school years}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Yes, more - during school years that was very, very important to know where you were. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They certainly made it their business to - to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have to be home by a set time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not necessarily, no. You naturally would be but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It wasn't imposed on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, it wasn't imposed on you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It seems to have been a very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 relaxed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, it - let us say they was - in our school years that they kn
ew that some of your chums was having a bit of a party, birthday party or something like that, well you wouldn't have worried, it might have been ten or eleven o'clock before you come home but - if you were just merely with a few chums well - depended a l
ot on the time of the year you see, in wintertime you'd have got home before dark and - but in summertime, oh well - you just carried on, you got home - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It was late until quite late wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Well fact of the matter you know the - if it's really clear weather you see it's practically daylight right round here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you get any pocket money before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much, you see, well you got pocket money but - it wasn't pocket money generally as far as I remember - you
 got maybe a few coppers with you but it - that was generally for to buy your - well we used to get from the shop, there was a baker, there was a bakery almost next door to the school and - they always had an awful amount of broken biscuits and you used t
o
 get maybe a pennyworth of these broken biscuits and you would maybe get a - well of course a penny was all you looked for in them days, that was maybe your pocket money, maybe a penny and - and in nine cases out of ten you maybe bought a pennyworth of br
oken biscuits or something like that for it and children like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was it a regular thing or just occasional?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, just occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You didn't expect it ever week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no. No, you didn't expect it neither every week neither every day. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Can you remember anything either in your schooldays or your teenage days in the way of concerts or music concerts or cinemas or plays or magic lantern shows or theatres, entertainment of that type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Plenty of - yes, there was quite a bit of
 concert work. There was - but mainly in connection with the church. And - the - well that was about the only thing of that nature that you - that you'd have had. And you wouldn't have had much - you would have maybe a sketch with two or three in it but a
ctual - coming to the extent of plays, no you just didn't have it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Magic lanterns or cinemas of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I canna remember my - I know - I've a feeling there was a magic lantern now and again in the Walls area but I cannot remember ever seein
g one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you used to go into Lerwick to visit your mother and step-father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Just very, very occasionally. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I don't think that I ever went in especially for that purpose. You had some other reason for going and then of course you probably stayed 
a night or so with them. But - I never remember - never recall just going to them for a holiday or anything of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they come and visit at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, occasionally you know but it wasn't easy you see, twenty-five mile distant you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 But mind you, you used to - it wasn't - it was quite usual for to travel it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember the very first time you went to Lerwick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I can. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 
I can remember very, very well indeed, especially when I went, I was eleven year old. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I 
was eleven year old and my uncle which I said that was finally lost with a ship and all hands and he was coming to Lerwick with a shop and he couldn't get away from the ship long enough to get to Walls so my aunt and my other uncle and my - and myself whe
n
 I was eleven year old, we started out and we traveled to Lerwick. And my mother at that time was staying out at Sound just over here and - we went up there, we came to Lerwick, we went out there, had something to eat, came back here to Lerwick, turned ar
o
und town all the time and - went home back to Sound here and - had a sleep. Next day - oh my uncle came ashore and was out at my mother's house like and - then - he took us off to the ship and we had a look at the ship and - she was lying off in the harbo
ur, had to go out in a boat, and started off and traveled back to Walls the next day. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You remember that so clearly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I remember that very clearly, especially clearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you have a picture in your mind about how Lerwick would be do you think, did you like it when you saw it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I suppose I did, the only thing was it was all very - I mean I couldn't - I couldn't have gone back next day and - and found where I'd been or found the street or found how to get through to the town and to
 my mother's, I couldn't have gone back next day and found that, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It seemed confusing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Absolutely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was six year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
I think it was - now let's see, I'm not clear on that, I think it was half past nine. I think so. And four o'clock I think was finished up. Roughly very - very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 near the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  same hours here now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 As soon as you started school did you always stay on for the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What kind of school was it, aboard school or a church school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, it's a board school, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well it would not have taken me about a quarter of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You were quite near to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - just about a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - there was - I could go from two sides, there 
was a road leading below the croft and a road leading above the croft and there were children going from both sides so I could either go with the one lot or the other. And the - the road that led - the road that led past - above the house as I should call
 
it was the same people I told you about before, that I played with and I - which the one that became my wife, and then down below was those that came from another hamlet, a hamlet of about seven or eight houses and went that road. And so I could go either
 of two, I could just join the one crowd or the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you taken on your very first day to school do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I was taken along but I canna - I canna remember - I know I would have been taken along, I'm pretty certain of that, but I cou
ldn't say if I remember it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I didn't come home, I went to a friend's house. Yes. Near the school, yes, down in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And that was a regular thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You don't recollect any payment being made for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, I can't say that there was ever any payment, never to my knowledge, there was definitely that as I say something given in kind but never - never in money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh I - I liked - well I liked school but still I've always said afterwards that I never - many people says oh my schooldays were my best days, but no, I never - I never wish to be back at school again. But I liked it and I reckon I was a very very average
 pupil but - no, I - that - something - no I didn't like - I didn't like the - never dreamed about going back to it again, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you say there was something tired about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I would say, there's - something tied about it I said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You felt tied down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes. Yes. Too much tied down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How many teachers were there at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
There was two. There was just a pupil teacher and a - and a head teacher. And you were in - oh you might be there - I think there was three or four - all in the same category but changes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 But there were always two teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 There were always two, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember what you thought of the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I generally speaking I seemed to liked them all right. I don't remember ever having - anything really against them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they come from crafting families, were they sort of the same class as most of the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 They just - no, no, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 these}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  teachers nearly in every case came from the South. Yes, nearly in every case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you re
member the things that they said were important for you to do, I mean for example manners and tidiness, punctuality or how you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 No, I couldn't - I couldn't say - you - I got more of that maybe from home as what I ever felt was taught in the sch
ool, it was just more or less the usual - reading, arithmetic and - - blackboard work and such like, I canna remember them ever sort of - putting manners into it or - or discipline of any kind, I never remember that.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What about how children spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I don't - I don't think there was - can't remember anything - special about that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Younger people here tell me that at school they tell them not to speak the dialect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - I canna - - I canna recall anything of that kind in the early days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the home you spoke the dialect as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Generally speaking, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember how it was that you learned to speak as you're speaking now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - I think that that just came very naturally to me when I mixed so much with strangers in - say in the Merchant Navy and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not so much before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It wasn't something that was ingrained in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, it wasn't. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What would happen, well it was out with the hand and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was that quite frequent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes. Quite frequent, oh yes, you didn't need to transgress very far because - before the strap came down I can assure you. It was a strap, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you think it was more than necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well - that's a difficult question, I - I suppose we maybe thought at it was too much of it, it wasn't necessary but - I often think since that - probably maybe was necessary. In many cases. I - I can
 - I never can recall any of the teachers being obsessed with that idea, I mean to say, they were - reasonable fair people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were the girls punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What type of things was it, both behaviour and bad work that you were punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, more - more behaviour of course. But - you would have got it for work as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was an interest in hour schoolwork shown by your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Yes, yes, they - they - liked to see you getting on and - just as folk would do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they ask you what you did at school and visit the school and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Occasionally, no, they - I wouldn't say they ever visited the school but there wasn't - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  more of that these - today, having the certa
in periods that they invite teachers along and also discuss the standard of their education and that with parents, but no there wasn't much of that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they meet the teachers in any way, did your uncle and aunts know the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. Not particularly, they - they wouldn't have any special connection with them or they wouldn't have had any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Any means of meeting them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember the teachers singling out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, that was - something that I cannot ever recall, I don't think I ever saw any - unfairness that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were there any gangs or cliques or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much, there was - there maybe an occasional - roughneck that want
ed to - to rule - to rule all the rest and that but I couldn't - I couldn't recall any cliques.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In some schools I've heard that children would join up in cliques from different parts of the community, it wasn't like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, no, there was nothing like that, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember any children who were left out of thing for one reason or another, outcast in anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not very much, I couldn't say that I could ever recall anyone being at that stage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember any children who were simple minded in any way or severely incapacitated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Not very much, but there was a - there was a - slightly that but - you see - a great lot of people that was a wee bit - I mean wasn't just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 compos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 mentis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 , today they would be - try to - they would
 try to train them in some shape or form naturally but then a days I think if a child was anywhere severely handicapped they would just be kept at home altogether. And you see education wasn't compulsory. So I can't recall anyone in that stage, I - I can 
recall one or two that I would call always dunces, as you would say, that they couldn't - they couldn't drill anything into them but - I can never recall anyone being physically or mentally handicapped to the stage where they had to be specially treated.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No, I certainly would not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. Nothing whatever, nothing whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You never went to navigational classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No - well I - no, I never went to navigational classes as long - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 
sometimes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 after I had been at sea at Merchant Navy, that's the first time that I remember anything in the line of classes, I remember through the recreation club there they got a navigation class goi
ng and there was a - a skipper in the district at the time and I think he was taking navigation classes at school as well and he had an effort - made an effort at - and I'll tell you a story about that. The very man that you have interviewed, Hugh Cumming
.
 And he was one of the class and you know Hughie was a signalman in the Navy, I don't know if he ever told you that or not, but he was a signalman in the Navy and - you couldn't - this chap he tried to get us off with the flags you know, the flag signalin
g and also the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 Morse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 lamp. And no he couldn't get Hughie to do anything of that kind. At last he got him persuaded to try it and when he started off with the flags and the signaling the - the teacher couldn't follow him at all. He just - just left the teach
er standing with - and gasping at him. Oh yes, Hughie was - Hughie was far}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 far ahead of anything that the teacher could teach when he once got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 in to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No I don't. I feel that - I was, as I
 said before, I was probably a very average pupil and - I don't think - I mean, I've been happy with every job that I've gone to and I don't think that I would have liked to have been anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you think you benefitted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Oh yes, yes, there's no question about that. At least, I mean to say, you got to the stage where you could read and write and - and speak sensibly and such like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 What room did you bath in, in those days?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh well you just - washed down as best you could and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 In the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well, not always very often in the kitchen, generally you tried to - the only way you could escape to was to go into the butend room, the best room. And shut the door. It was a lot more private. Especially when you came on a wee bit of age you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Ah well - I - I - I reckon that you were eating meat fairly often. Not - not of course the meat, not cow's meat but mutton and - things of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And a bit of pork you had too didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Bit of pork, yes. Oh I - I'm afraid that that would have - at least every second day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And other days you had fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You would very often have fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 How often in a week do you think you'd have a whole day when you didn't have meat or fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 It wouldn't be very many days, you might have - must - must - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 might}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  have one day or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Not more than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember the custom of one place in the middle from which people helped themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No - yes, I know what you're getting at. Well there was - not exactly - well you always got that with potatoes of course. You always got your potatoes put on one big plate. And when I come to think of it, yes,
 right enough the mutton and that would have been the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You wouldn't have had individual plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
No, the only - the - when you were young and the like of that they would probably have dished out certain bits for you and cut it for you and that kind of thing but - generally speaking you served yourself off the communal plate. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And didn't have your own plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. Of course you had - you had your side plates there and you took it on your side plate you see but it was taken from a communal plate.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did they say you should hit back if another child hurt you or did they tell you not to defend yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I don't think it ever arose as you say because - I think you just sort of use your own discretion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You don't remember running to your aunt or your mother or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I can't - no, I - no, I canna remember ever telling me to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You just grew up hitting back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, if it was - if you felt it was necessary, yes. If you felt the chap was a bit bigger t
han you you tried to run as fast as you could and get away from him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 If you had any worried as a small child could you take them to anybody in the family or did you keep them to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well I can't remember very much really worries but I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 undoudtedly}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 would have taken them to - well - it would have been my - own - my kitchen aunt as I would say, they call that the one who used to stay around the house I think was my sort of favourite, so probably it I had have worried that - I would probably hav
e gone to her but I don't remember ever any particular case of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you remember having nightmares or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, I never remember - I just remember one. One that even I - to speak about right up to this day - on our hous
e was a - a porch, a big porch, huge thing it was. It was - fact of the matter once a time - upon a time my uncle used to use it was a workshop. And - after he built another workshop for himself, was a joiners shop then they used it for keeping the bits i
n
 and - water, of course water had to be taken by bucket from the well you see and all these kind of things was kept there. And - I remember this nightmare of this thing - well, if you could describe the devil then it must have been him because this thing 
was a black hairy creature and I'd apparently fancied myself going up taking some peats and this thing had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16398863\charrsid12791982 caught}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
 hold of me in the dark porch you see and was dragging me across buckets and all kinds of things. I wakened up screaming, I had that - that right on my mind today as clear as it was then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Would you say that your mother was as easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh I think so. Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 You kept in contact after she went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes, very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And how did you get on with your step-father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Quite well.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982  Oh yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in the conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Yes, more or less, there was nobody just ever - well occasionally they would have said, oh, wait - wait 'til so and 
so's spoken, you see but generally speaking we weren't had - we weren't kept down in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember what they thought about swearing or didn't it arise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, they didn't - they didn't like to hear you swear. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Did it ever happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well - I doubt it did but - but they - generally speaking would have corrected you there right away. Oh no, didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Can you remember ever being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I cannot remember ever being really thrashed. Never in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Do you ever remember getting any kind of a slap or a hit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Well - they might have in a very small way but - there were nothing - nothing that I can remember, nothing - nothing that I can recall. I many a time got a severe telling off but never to use the hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Any other kind of punishment, being deprived of anything like being told to stay indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. No, no, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16148208\charrsid12791982 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982  was nothing of that. No, no. That - that kind of thing, never saw that in our house at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Were you never deprived of food as a punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no, absolutely definitely not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 So really you can say the only thing you remember is a telling off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Well it - more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 What sort of things, can you remember any particular occasion when you were told off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 
Yes, I - I do remember one occasion when I was very severely told off about that. Another chap, the same chap that's home from South Shields just now and I - we'd been out and that was on a Sunday. And - probably nobody had seen us but we had
 been throwing stones and that and one of the stones had gone through a skylight or a small window and - outhouse. And of course you know that being on a Sunday that was just a - and I - I went and told them I wouldn't - I didn't want them to find it out 
I'd rather tell it than be found out and the point you see - and I remember - I think my grandfather still alive somehow or another because I - I think it was him that did the - did the more - gave me the biggest howling about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 And you remember that well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 I do remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Was there any betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13764832 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5662026 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737622\charrsid12791982 No. No. I never knew - not - no, not a - I don't remember that in the village at all.
